<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871215-0072 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Unisys Corp.</HL><DD> 12/15/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> UISBUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK) </IN><TEXT>   Unisys Corp. said its board authorized the purchase of as many as 10 million of the computer maker's common shares.    The Blue Bell, Pa.-based concern said it would buy back the shares through Dec. 31, 1988, or purchase preferred shares convertible into 10 million common shares. The company won't begin the buy-back until next year.    Unisys, which has 149.2 million common and 28.5 million preferred shares outstanding as of Sept. 30, said the shares would be retired, used to fund the company's stock-option plan or other benefits and other corporate purposes.    In New York Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday, Unisys closed at $32.50, up $2. </TEXT></DOC>